Pre-Game Insights: Both Angola and Namibia are out to win their first-ever knockout game at the Africa Cup of Nations.
Angola went through the group stage unbeaten and as group winners.
Namibia stunned Tunisia to win their first AFCON match before qualifying in third place of Group E.
Angola captain Fredy and Bruno Paz both came off with knocks in their last game.
Namibia made changes after a heavy defeat to South Africa and drew with Mali to reach the knockouts, with Ryan Nyambe and Petrus Shitembi hoping for a recall.
Pedro Goncalves' Angola is expected to have the firepower to punish Namibia's flimsy defence.
Angola are unbeaten in their fixtures against Namibia, with 6 wins and 6 draws.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is scheduled for a 5pm GMT kick-off on Saturday, January 27, 2024, at Stade de la Paix in Bouake.
In the UK, the game will be televised live on Sky Sports Football, with coverage starting at 4.55pm.
Subscribers can also catch the contest live online via the Sky Go app.
Angola to qualify odds: 6/10, Namibia to qualify odds: 6/5.
